.TH TPLOTTER 1 "December 2025" "tplotter 1.0.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
tplotter \- terminal function plotter
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B tplotter
[\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.I EXPRESSION
[\fIEXPRESSION\fR...]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B tplotter
is a simple command-line tool for plotting mathematical functions in the terminal using ASCII art.
It supports multiple functions on the same plot with color-coded output.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Display help message and exit.
.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\-version
Display version information and exit.
.SH EXPRESSIONS
Mathematical expressions can contain:
.TP
.B Variables
x (the independent variable)
.TP
.B Operators
+ (addition), - (subtraction), * (multiplication), / (division), ^ (power)
.TP
.B Functions
sin(x), cos(x), tan(x) - trigonometric functions
.br
log(x) - base-10 logarithm
.br
ln(x) - natural logarithm
.br
sqrt(x) - square root
.br
exp(x) - exponential function
.TP
.B Constants
pi - Ï€ (3.14159...)
.br
e - Euler's number (2.71828...)
.SH EXAMPLES
Plot sine function:
.RS
.B tplotter "sin(x)"
.RE

Plot multiple functions:
.RS
.B tplotter "sin(x)" "cos(x)" "x^2/10"
.RE

Plot complex expression:
.RS
.B tplotter "sin(x)^2 + cos(x)^2"
.RE

Plot with constants:
.RS
.B tplotter "sin(2*pi*x)"
.RE
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success
.TP
.B 1
Invalid expression or other error
